15/06/2004
LISBON, Portugal -- An unexpectedly powerful Swedish side dimmed Bulgaria's hopes of a rerun of its 1994 World Cup success. 
The Swedes thrashed Bulgaria 5-0 in the two teams' opening European Championship match on Monday (14 June).
In other news, European football's governing body has warned Croatia that it would be charged with improper conduct after five of its players were booked in the team's opening match against Switzerland. 
The UEFA meets late Tuesday to decide Croatia's punishment. 
(AP, Reuters, AFP, Bloomberg - 14/06/04)
